Business Brief -- Harris Corp.:
   Electronics Firm Posts Net
   For Fiscal Second Quarter
In the quarter ended Dec. 27, earnings totaled 49 cents a
share, at the high end of analysts' expectations. Revenue
fell 1% to $755.7 million from $765.4 million.
   For the first half, the Melbourne, Fla., company posted
earnings of $32 million, or 82 cents a share, compared with a
yearearlier loss of $38.3 million, or 97 cents a share.
Revenue fell almost 3% to $1.44 billion from $1.48 billion.